{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Build a Portable Random Noise Audio Jammer for Less than $50","date":"21 May 2019","path":"/audio-jammer","author":"Jered Higgins","excerpt":"With the increasing amount of new surveillance systems, wide use of surveillance devices/software, and lack of tools/resources/education on privacy issues - why not try to maintain some amount of privacy?","tags":["blog","projects","privacy"],"coverImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.2138284250960307,"src":"/static/0665f7a6cd363373ba506b9d5a89b12c/bc3a8/audio-jammer.jpg","srcSet":"/static/0665f7a6cd363373ba506b9d5a89b12c/d278e/audio-jammer.jpg 200w,\n/static/0665f7a6cd363373ba506b9d5a89b12c/8539d/audio-jammer.jpg 400w,\n/static/0665f7a6cd363373ba506b9d5a89b12c/bc3a8/audio-jammer.jpg 800w,\n/static/0665f7a6cd363373ba506b9d5a89b12c/81ef8/audio-jammer.jpg 1200w,\n/static/0665f7a6cd363373ba506b9d5a89b12c/989b1/audio-jammer.jpg 1600w,\n/static/0665f7a6cd363373ba506b9d5a89b12c/5af94/audio-jammer.jpg 2844w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}}},"id":"9bbd450e-3bf9-5feb-a1fd-17c029d7f52a","html":"<hr>\n<h2>Purpose and Background:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Make an affordable and portable random noise generator for counter-surveillance/privacy</li>\n</ul>\n<p>With the increasing amount of new surveillance systems, wide use of surveillance devices/software, and lack of tools/resources/education on privacy issues - <strong>why not try to maintain some amount of privacy?</strong></p>\n<hr>\n<h2>Resources:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.eff.org/pages/tools\">EFF Tools</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://sec.eff.org/\">EFF Security Education</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mass_surveillance_in_the_United_States\">Wikipedia Mass Surveillance Portal</a> </li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2>Supplies:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Arduino UNO $22.00</li>\n<li>9V Battery $4.00</li>\n<li>9V Battery Snap Connector $4.00</li>\n<li>Jumper Wires $2.00</li>\n<li>8 ohm speaker $2.00</li>\n<li>Photoresistor $1.00</li>\n<li>4.7K ohm resistor $0.75</li>\n<li>100 ohm resistor $0.50</li>\n<li>Half-size solderless breadboard $5.00</li>\n<li>\n<p>Assortment of Lego bricks $4.00</p>\n<hr>\n<p>Total Cost: $45.25</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<h2>Software:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.arduino.cc/en/Main/Software\">Arduino IDE</a></p>\n<hr>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Circuit/Schematic:</h2>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 600px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 64.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"circuit\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/5db70014d38467d6af981b5f267b67c3/7aa3b/circuit.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5db70014d38467d6af981b5f267b67c3/563d8/circuit.png 200w,\n/static/5db70014d38467d6af981b5f267b67c3/7c2ef/circuit.png 400w,\n/static/5db70014d38467d6af981b5f267b67c3/7aa3b/circuit.png 600w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 84.42136498516322%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"schematic\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/0fcc161cbf300afb94e7b43eac46f63a/86d96/schematic.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0fcc161cbf300afb94e7b43eac46f63a/563d8/schematic.png 200w,\n/static/0fcc161cbf300afb94e7b43eac46f63a/7c2ef/schematic.png 400w,\n/static/0fcc161cbf300afb94e7b43eac46f63a/86d96/schematic.png 674w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<h2>Code:</h2>\n<p>I used some <a href=\"http://www.arduino.cc/en/Tutorial/Tone2\">example code</a> in public domain with a small tweak to generate a tone out that relies on the sensor reading. Adjust the settings to find a sound that isn't too annoying. See code and instructions below:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"csharp\"><pre class=\"language-csharp\"><code class=\"language-csharp\"><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> outputPin <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">9</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">setup</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// initialize serial communications (for debugging only):</span>\n  Serial<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">begin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">9600</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">loop</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// read the sensor:</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> sensorReading <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">analogRead</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>A0<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// map the analog input range (400 - 1000 from the photoresistor)</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// to the output pitch range (120 - 1500Hz)</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> thisPitch <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">map</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>sensorReading<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">400</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1000</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">120</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1500</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// play the pitch:</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">tone</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>outputPin<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> thisPitch<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// delay in between reads for stability</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">delay</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>        \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>","excerpt":"Purpose and Background:Make an affordable and portable random noise generator for counter-surveillance/privacyWith the increasing amount of…"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"type":"posts","next":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/value-of-attention","title":"The Value of Attention","tags":["blog","obiter-dictum"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/jered/Desktop/website/blog/src/posts/value-of-attention.md"},"previous":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/updates-new-drawings","title":"Updates and New Drawings for Genesis Book Series","tags":["blog","genesis","drawings"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/jered/Desktop/website/blog/src/posts/updates-new-drawings.md"}}}